  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aimed to evaluate the longitudinal association between n-6:n-3 LCPUFAs ratio in
      cord blood and child ADHD symptoms at 4 and 7 years old. This study was based on the INMA
      project, a population-based birth cohort in Spain. Higher cord blood n-6:n-3 ratio was
      associated with higher subclinical ADHD symptoms during early and mid-childhood.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
